JUDGES: András Sajó;Françoise Tulkens;Guido Raimondi;Kristina Pardalos;Nona Tsotsoria
TEXT: The applicant , Ms Krisztina Felcser , is a NORP national who was born in DATE and lives in GPE . She was represented before the ORG by Mr ORG , a lawyer practising in GPE . ORG ( “ the Government ” ) were represented by PERSON , Agent , ORG and Law Enforcement .
The facts of the case , as submitted by the parties , may be summarised as follows .

On DATE an action was brought with a view to evicting the applicant from her service flat . A first - instance decision , requiring the applicant to vacate the flat and the plaintiff to arrange for alternative accommodation , was adopted on DATE . Part of this judgment was quashed and remitted on DATE . ORG gave judgment on DATE . On DATE ORG reversed this decision and established the fee payable by the applicant for the past use of the flat . On DATE ORG rejected the applicant 's petition for review .

In the meantime , the applicant filed a motion for execution against the plaintiff in respect of her claim for alternative accommodation . On DATE and CARDINAL DATE the LOC and ORG respectively rejected this motion , observing that this claim was not enforceable until the applicant vacated the flat .
